cs.VLSI, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.ET, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.VLSI - The paper proposes a technique to protect Intellectual Property (IP) in the semiconductor supply chain by camouflaging interconnects using multiplexers. This falls under the domain of VLSI design and security. 
2. cs.CR - The paper discusses security attacks such as Trojan insertion, cloning, counterfeiting, reverse engineering, and piracy of IP. These are all related to computer security and hence, the paper could also belong to the category of Cryptography and Security. 
3. cs.SE - The paper proposes a new technique for camouflaging interconnects to protect IP. This falls under the domain of software engineering as it involves designing and implementing a new technique. 
4. cs.ET - The paper discusses the use of transistor threshold voltage to prevent reverse engineering of the proposed camouflaging technique. This falls under the domain of electronic devices and circuits. 
5. cs.AR - The paper proposes a technique to hide the original connectivity of the net using multiplexers. This falls under the domain of augmented reality as it involves creating a virtual layer of protection over the original design.
